flowRoot.flowPara: su - user open a shell as user
chown user:group file change owner:group of
chgrp group file change group of file
chmod MODE file change file permissions
ls list files in work directory
ls -a list all files (including hidden files)
cp file dest copy file to dest
cp -r directory dest copy directory to dest
mv source dest move/rename file/directory to
ln -s file link create symbolic link of file
mount -t type device mount-point mount device
mount -o loop iso mount-point mount iso image
$ yum provides */pkg check what provides pkg
$ yum info pkg get pkg information
$ yum history get installed packages history
$ rpm -q pkg get installed pkg version
$ yum clean all clean the cache
# iwlist scan scan for wireless networks
# service iptables start/stop start or stop
allow or reject connection to port
$ service daemon status view daemon status
set service to run/not run in runlevels 3,5
Ctrl+Alt+Bksp restart X display if frozen*
Ctrl+Alt+F1 switch back to X display

text.tspan: * Use carefully, especially with the -f option.

flowRoot.flowPara: Adult supervision required for using scissors

openSUSE believes in choice and doesn't limit it. We also believe in making it easy for you to make decisions, and giving you the same seamless experience with openSUSE you'll get with any choices you make. We believe in adjusting your system to you, and no matter what route you take or what you try to achieve,
you're never alone with the openSUSE community. So make your choice, and choose openSUSE.
